==English==
===Etymology===
{{wikipedia}}
: The origin of this expression is uncertain, but it is likely that it arose in the American southwest during the late 1800s.

===Idiom===
'''mexican standoff'''
# {{slang}} A Mexican standoff is a slang term for a situation where two or more [[opponents]] have weapons aimed directly at each other, so that neither can attack the other without being attacked themselves. This [[situation]] might cause the [[participants]] to consider [[diplomacy]], or plain-out [[surrender]].